	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok.. several points REALLY need to be raised here. <BR>
<BR>
Tink bags are NOT cheap. It took me a long time to be able to afford just one of them and at 5,250pp a pop (the CHEAPEST that they can be bought for), Tink Bags are not an option except for higher level characters. Even then, it is rae to see someone with more than one. Thus Tink Bags are not really an option.<BR>
<BR>
Tailored bags are much easier to get and will now be in huge demand. As the 10 slot Handmade Backpacks go for 100pp I would be very surprised to see the Lg. Tailored Bags go for anywhere NEAR that kind of cash. More so since low level tailors can make them and they are everywhere. I am sure that Master Tailors such as myself will be busy making Handmade Backpacks left and right. This increase in demand will likely drive the price of the HQ Bear Pelt up from 30pp to an even higher price (tho I wish it didn't). That in turn will likely cause the price of the Handmade Backpacks to go up even higher than they are now. I would caution ppl to be careful and not let greed drive prices outta the range of the players who need the bags and backpacks the most, lower level players. Just stick to the existing prices, please.<BR>
<BR>
As for the spell grimoires, etc. whose weight did not change, I look for VI to change that as soon as they realize it.<BR>
<BR>
Bottom line is that the ppl who are effected the MOST by this change are the lower level characters (especially monks) who need to scrimp and save on pounds where ever they could. Since Lg. Sewing Kits can hold ANY size item AND weighed very little, they were perfect for starting characters. Now those same starting characters will find themselves with a lot of extra weight. Most will see an increase of about 10 to 12 pounds depending upon what containers they were using.<BR>
<BR>
One of the unfortunate things I see happening as a result of this change is that ppl won't play casters as much simply cause the don't want to go through the hassle of the weight problem now made worse by the this patch. It would not surprise me at all to see ppl whose main is a 20 - 29 lvl caster, shelve that character and create an Ogre or Troll character (maybe a barbarian? or dwarf?).<BR>
<BR>
One suggestion would be to make the Lg. Tailored Bags 8 slots instead of 6. For Monks, maybe VI could have a newbie quest where Monks (and maybe others) could do an easy quest that would give them a low weight container that could hold up to large items. Since Monks need more than one, the item should NOT be Lore but could be made No Drop if they wanted only Monks to get it.<BR>
<BR>
Xarkof<BR>
Shining Alliance<BR>
47th Necro of the Prexus Server
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
