	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Since I've been directly questioned, I feel obligated to offer a rebuttle.<BR>
<BR>
A large sewing kit will run approxamately 2pp.  A little under, but for an estimate that's about right.  I am not familiar with the costs of a Low Quality Bear Pelt and a silk cord on your server, but those materials will probably run about 5gp.  LQ Bears aren't exactly a hot commodity.<BR>
<BR>
Now, if you absolutly must tailor on the run, pick up a small sewing kit.  The weight is 0.4 and can tailor those nonstackable silks together.  I admit, it cannot make silk cords, but you have your 8 slot kit back at home in the bank, right?  A small sewing kit can also make anything with a pelt and a pattern, so there we have the pelts taken care of.  Anything relating to silk, I will also conceed, requires a large kit, but the results from that don't stack, so why bother making those on the run?<BR>
<BR>
I find you, Ardarius, a hypocrite in suggesting we purchase 11pp 4 slot containers when our issue here is trying to save money.  You simply seem to be looking for the easy solution.  I think getting a 6 slot bag (doesn't have to be weight reducing, still .8 to 1 wt) and a small sewing kit would be plenty to start with.  To add, large bags cost about, maybe, 4-5 gold from merchants.  Even more in the cost range of young monks.  I don't think a 0.4 to 0.6 weight difference that early will mean much  (-8<BR>
<BR>
Some more global comments, if you're concerned about weight and you have many general inventory slots open because you can't carry backpacks in them, get smaller containers.  For the 3 wt an 8 slot backpack takes, you can get 3 1wt large bags that hold the exact same things, and instead get 18 slots.  Plenty of room for all those 0.1 wt drops.  I'm also very surprised at the lack of knowledge of the small sewing kit.  For every monk looking for a light way to combine those silks, I say again, look at this kit!<BR>
<BR>
And no, a pelt wouldn't make a sewing kit smell any nicer...but you don't leave it in the kit that long.<BR>
<BR>
I hope this covers some concerns.  Just remember, large tailoring kits and backpacks are not the only containers in the game!  Those smaller ones are beautiful for us with weight limitations.<BR>
<BR>
--Kassara Stilfyre, 27th monk of the Ashen Order, member of Fantasy, Vazaelle
				</font>
			</td>

