			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think the most important feedback for EQ that I noticed between last weeks patch, the emergency patch and this patch, is pay more attention to core engine issues please.<BR>
<BR>
Last weeks patch apparently caused major problems with certain video cards, even though the patch seemed to have little to do with core engine issues.  The emergency patch caused huge instability at least on my machine evidenced by frequent crashes on zoning.  Yesterday's patch seems to have fixed this.  Please, please, please place a higher priority on keeping the core engine stable, regression testing, and multiple video card testing than on game play issues.<BR>
<BR>
As far as the changes in weight to trade containers, I can understand that its reasonable for my ranger who has been carrying around 2 fletching kits and 2 sewing kits should probably learn enough additional sewing skills to make himself a couple of backpacks.  He'll also be donating these skills to anyone bringing him a pelt and pattern.  On the other hand there is a real need for some characters to carry around a sewing kit, and the weight of that should not be so high.  As an ironic twist, perhaps the 2 slot sewing kit should be very light in weight.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
