	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To: Gayorg level 51 whatcha ma digger<BR>
<BR>
Obviously you are an ebayer.  Verant does or at least tries to do something called risk/reward.  The sewing kits are the only viable option for light weight bags for Kunark residents.  I have 4 level 20-35 iksars all use a combo of backpack and sewing kits.  Why? There are NO bears in Kunark, no low/mid level mob drops, and very few trader offering the packs.  The best we can make with our resources are small/medium item containers ... things that use cat or wolf skins.  Maybe we could find someone to make a tailor quiver..6 slot medium items.<BR>
<BR>
At level 1-4, a char can easily kill enough skellies to get the plat for large sewing kits (most zones).  A non-twinked char (yes, they exist) has to save a long time for a handmade pack, if it is even available.<BR>
<BR>
At level 35+, the kunarkians can maybe get a dusty ransaker 6 slot 25% reduction pack from Kaesora.<BR>
<BR>
BTW, at what level did you first save enough to get a tinker bag?  I have a level 51 char, the bags are way out of my reach - i chose not to buy because i could use the money for other things.<BR>
<BR>
Also, if you even use the done/close button on a combinable container you are a fool and deserve to loose the contents on a miss click.  You can close the container the same way you open it - with a right-click on the inventory slot or a left click to pick the item up out of the slot.<BR>
<BR>
Sllaassli<BR>
24th season<BR>
17wt prepatch, 35+ post patch<BR>

