			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Guys, the trade kits were never INTENDED to be used as backpacks. It was an oversight. They didn't do anything sooner because they felt the risk of them eating everything in them on a mis-click was sufficient to offset the bonus of the weight. BUT, too many people complained about losing sever THOUSAND plat worth of items to misclicks... So, they removed that risk. This in turn made lightweight backpacks at ZERO risk that were far too good for the ease in obtaining them...hence, the weight increase.<BR>
<BR>
VI, as I see it, intended from the start for us to WORK to obtain large capacity, lightweight packs.<BR>
<BR>
Besides, think about it: How silly is it for a large sewing kit that's so lightweight to be able to carry EIGHT STEEL BREASTPLATES?
				</font>
			</td>

